  <num>KL-CY-2026-001</num>
  <heading>Kiowa Tribe Juvenile Procedures Act</heading>
  <meta>
    <effective>2026-02-28</effective>
    <history>
      <adopted>2026-02-14</adopted>
    </history>
    <citations>
      <citation type="res" url="./adopted/KL-CY-2026-001.pdf">KL-CY-2026-001</citation>
    </citations>
  </meta>
  <recitals>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text> the Kiowa Tribe is a federally recognized Indian Tribe with a Constitution approved by the Secretary of the Interior; and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text> the Legislature, is vested with the authority to pass laws and resolutions pursuant to <cite doc="Constitution of the Kiowa Tribe">Article VI, Section 6 (a) of the Constitution of the Kiowa Tribe</cite>; and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text> the Legislature is authorized under the Kiowa Constitution and is empowered to promulgate and enforce codes and laws, to protect Kiowa Tribal Citizens; and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>	the Kiowa Legislature has previously created a Juvenile Division of the Kiowa Trial Court (see Legislative Resolution KL-CY-2023-010); and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text> this Kiowa Tribe Juvenile Procedures Act is intended to secure Kiowa children care and guidance that will best serve their welfare, the interest of the Kiowa Tribe, and society in general.</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>NOW, THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED,</conjunction>
      <text> the Kiowa Tribe Legislature, having been delegated certain authorities under the Kiowa Constitution, the governing body of the Kiowa Tribe, does hereby adopt the attached "Kiowa Tribe Juvenile Procedures Act."</text>
    </recital>
  </recitals>
